# UI Design Principles - MOBILE FIRST

## Critical Mobile UX Rules
- **Icons over text for actions**: Use symbols (×, +, -, ↑, ↓, etc.) instead of words like "Remove", "Delete", "Add"
- **No text buttons on mobile**: Actions should be icon-only with compact touch targets (28-32px square)
- **Minimize visual noise**: Every pixel counts on mobile - remove all non-essential elements
- **Single-line layouts**: Items in lists must fit on one line with proper flexbox constraints
- **Touch-friendly**: All interactive elements must be at least 44×44px tap target (can be 28px visual with padding)
- **Test mobile first**: Design and test for mobile viewport (375px width) before desktop

## Space Efficiency
- **Maximize functional space**: Prioritize content and interactive elements over decorative elements
- **Minimize unnecessary chrome**: Avoid large titles, redundant headings, or decorative containers unless explicitly requested
- **Default to compact layouts**: Use minimal padding/margins (8-12px on mobile, 10-20px on desktop)
- **Remove redundant labels**: If the purpose is obvious from context, skip the heading entirely

## Layout Guidelines
- Main content (charts, data, forms) should occupy 90%+ of viewport space
- Control panels should be compact and dense - every row matters on mobile
- Default chart/canvas heights should be generous (500px+) to maximize data visibility
- Use subtle backgrounds (#f5f5f5, #fafafa) instead of gradients
- All list items must use `min-width: 0` and `flex-shrink` to prevent wrapping

## Interactive Elements
- **Buttons**: Icon-only by default. Add `title` attribute for accessibility
- **Inputs**: Minimal borders, compact sizing (8px padding max)
- **Lists**: Single line per item, flexible name fields, fixed-width value fields
- **Color indicators**: 16-20px squares maximum, not 30px+
- **Card padding**: 8-10px maximum, not 15-20px

## When Building Tools/Playgrounds
- Focus on the interactive element first (e.g., the chart should dominate the page)
- Controls should be minimal and functional - one line per control if possible
- Skip all decorative titles unless user explicitly asks for polish
- Use simple, clean styling that doesn't compete with content
- No emojis in headings unless specifically requested

## Visual Hierarchy
- Let functionality speak for itself
- Use minimal shadows (0 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.08)) or none
- Smaller everything: 16-20px color indicators, 8-10px padding, 28px icon buttons
- Avoid text where icons suffice

## When to Add Polish
- Only add decorative elements when the user explicitly requests "polished", "beautiful", or "modern" design
- If building a prototype or tool - default to extreme functional minimalism
- When in doubt, optimize for mobile information density and usability over aesthetics
- Remember: The user will complain if there's too much visual noise on mobile

## Flexbox Best Practices for Mobile
- Use `flex: 1` and `min-width: 0` on text inputs to allow shrinking
- Use `flex-shrink: 0` on buttons and fixed-width inputs
- Use `white-space: nowrap` on buttons to prevent wrapping
- Test that items stay on one line at 375px width
